      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "If you do this you'd have to update `configure.ac` as well to detect the version and fail with a warning about the CVE if it's not recent enough.\r\n\r\nHowever, using CURVE makes very little sense in our use case. It is an encryption protocol for zmq, and our zmq notification is explicitly meant for *local* notifications. There's no possible use for encryption there. It's also not even possible to configure the socket as encrypting through `bitcoind` `-zmq*` parameters.\r\n\r\nAlso note that the version used in `depends` (which is used to build the binary distribution) is already `4.3.1` (oh, I see this is about 4.3.2, anyway, the above still holds).",
